    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-07-01T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-07-01T13:00:00-05:00" n="502"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d502">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">550.S1/1084: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hull</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-07-01T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 1, 1933—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 1—1:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>87. For the President and Phillips from Moley. Your telegram with objections to
                    declaration received. Note that it is based on first draft sent you but assume
                    no change in your opinion on basis of second draft sent this morning. Therefore
                    Secretary of State is issuing following statement: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The Secretary of State has received a reply from the President rejecting
                            the declaration in its present form. He will issue a statement of
                            American policy on the subject Monday.”<note n="6" xml:id="d502fn6">July
                                3.</note>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Will notify you of reaction of French and the Secretary will govern his statement
                    Monday in accordance therewith. Personally bow to your judgment with no
                    inconsiderable relief. Regards. [Moley.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
